<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Suncorp will shut down 20 branches around Australia as part of a major overhaul of the bank.</p>

<p>The closures include nine Queensland branches in response to the coronavirus pandemic and growing trend towards online banking. </p>

<p>The banking giant announced on Wednesday that over the counter transactions by customers have declined by almost 25 per cent in the 2019-20 financial year and plummeted 60 per cent in the last four years. </p>

<p>Branches to be closed include Beenleigh, Burpengary, Elanora, Hamilton, Sherwood, Stafford, Victoria Point, West End and Biloela in Queensland, the Courier Mail reported.</p>

<p>The closures follow reports earlier this week Suncorp plans to slash up 10 per cent of its staff as part of the bank restructure.</p>

<p>The number of job cuts are yet to be confirmed by the bank, which is Queensland's biggest company.</p>

<p>Daily Mail Australia has contacted Suncorp for more details regarding branch closures and job cuts. </p>

<p>Most Suncorp branches across Australia remain temporarily closed due to the ongoing coronavirus pandemic. </p>

